August 7, 2005 In the Beginning: I was born to goodly parents who did not attend any religious services. My father was force fed religion during his youth and swore he would not set foot inside another church when he was old enough to make his own decisions. As far as I know, he made good on that promise; except for weddings, and other special occasions, I don’t remember him ever attending any church services. My mother would have attended church, but deferred to my father on matters of religion. She didn’t attend church either, while my father was living. After my father died, at the age of 67, my mother started going to a Presbyterian church with my sister&mldr;

